What languages are available in the set known as Archenemy on the magic card market and having the code ARC?
SELECT DISTINCT `language` FROM set_translations WHERE `setCode` = 'ARC'	----- bird -----	card_games
What is the name of set number 5 and its translation?

SELECT `translation` FROM set_translations JOIN sets ON set_translations.`setCode` = sets.`code` WHERE sets.`id` = 5 AND sets.`name` IS NOT NULL GROUP BY sets.`name` ORDER BY sets.`name` ASC;	----- bird -----	card_games
What is the language and expansion type of set number 206?
SELECT DISTINCT `block` FROM sets WHERE `id` = 206	----- bird -----	card_games

SELECT DISTINCT sets.id FROM sets INNER JOIN set_translations ON sets.code = set_translations.setCode INNER JOIN foreign_data ON foreign_data.uuid = set_translations.setCode INNER JOIN cards ON cards.uuid = foreign_data.uuid WHERE sets.isFoilOnly = 1 AND foreign_data.language = 'Japanese' AND sets.isForeignOnly = 1;	----- bird -----	card_games
Which Russian set of cards contains the most cards overall?
DELETE FROM set_translations WHERE language IS NULL;	----- bird -----	card_games
What is the percentage of the set of cards that have Chinese Simplified as the language and are only available for online games?

SELECT (COUNT(*) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cards WHERE isOnlineOnly = 1)) AS percentage FROM cards INNER JOIN sets ON cards.`setCode` = (SELECT setCode FROM set_translations WHERE sets.`code` = set_translations.`setCode`) INNER JOIN foreign_data ON cards.`uuid` = foreign_data.`uuid` WHERE foreign_data.`language` = 'Chinese Simplified' AND sets.`isOnlineOnly` = 1	----- bird -----	card_games
How many sets are available just in Japanese and not in Magic: The Gathering Online?
SELECT T1.`setCode` FROM set_translations AS T1 INNER JOIN sets AS T2 ON T1.`setCode` = T2.`code` WHERE T1.`language` = 'Japanese' AND T2.`mtgoCode` IS NULL	----- bird -----	card_games
How many card border with black color ? List out the card id.
SELECT cards.`id` FROM cards WHERE cards.`borderColor` = 'black'	----- bird -----	card_games

SELECT id FROM cards WHERE frameEffects = 'extendedart'	----- bird -----	card_games

What is the language and flavor text of the card that has colorpie watermark? List out the type of this card.

SELECT DISTINCT T3.`type` FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN foreign_data AS T2 ON T1.`uuid` = T2.`uuid` INNER JOIN set_translations AS T3 ON T2.`setCode` = T3.`setCode` WHERE T1.`availability` LIKE '%colorpie%' AND T3.`language` = 'English' GROUP BY T3.`language` ORDER BY T3.`language` ASC;	----- bird -----	card_games
What is percentage of the cards with a converted Mana Cost of 10 in set of Abyssal Horror?

SELECT ROUND( ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN sets AS T2 ON T1.`setCode` = T2.`code` WHERE T2.`code` = ( SELECT `code` FROM sets WHERE `block` = 'Abyssal Horror' ) AND T1.`convertedManaCost` = 10 ) / ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN sets AS T2 ON T1.`setCode` = T2.`code` WHERE T2.`code` = ( SELECT `code` FROM sets WHERE `block` = 'Abyssal Horror' ) AND T1.`convertedManaCost` IS NOT NULL ) * 100, 2 ) AS percentage FROM cards WHERE `setCode` = ( SELECT `code` FROM sets WHERE `block` = 'Abyssal Horror' )	----- bird -----	card_games

SELECT DISTINCT set_translations.`setCode` FROM set_translations INNER JOIN ( SELECT * FROM sets WHERE type LIKE '%expansion%' UNION SELECT * FROM sets WHERE type LIKE '%Commander%' ) AS combined_sets ON set_translations.`setCode` = combined_sets.`code`	----- bird -----	card_games

SELECT DISTINCT T2.`name`, T2.`flavorText` FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN foreign_data AS T2 ON T1.`uuid` = T2.`uuid` INNER JOIN sets AS T3 ON T1.`setCode` = T3.`code` WHERE T1.`asciiName` LIKE '%abzan%' AND T2.`asciiName` IS NOT NULL AND T3.`type` = 'expansion' ORDER BY T2.`name` ASC;	----- bird -----	card_games

SELECT MIN(CAST(SUBSTR(time, 6) AS REAL)) AS lap_record FROM lapTimes JOIN races ON lapTimes.`raceId` = races.`raceId` WHERE races.`circuitId` = ( SELECT circuitId FROM circuits WHERE name = 'Yeongam County' );	----- bird -----	formula_1
Please list the lap records for the circuits in Italy.

SELECT T1.`lap`, T1.`time` FROM lapTimes AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.`raceId` = T2.`raceId` WHERE T2.`circuitId` IN ( SELECT circuitId FROM circuits WHERE country = 'Italy' )	----- bird -----	formula_1
In which Formula_1 race was the lap record for the Austrian Grand Prix Circuit set?

SELECT DISTINCT s.year FROM seasons s JOIN races r ON s.year = r.year JOIN circuits c ON r.circuitId = c.circuitId JOIN lapTimes lt ON r.raceId = lt.raceId AND c.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit' WHERE lt.time = ( SELECT MIN(time) AS fastest_lap_time FROM lapTimes WHERE raceId = r.raceId AND circuitId = c.circuitId );	----- bird -----	formula_1
In the race a driver set the lap record for the Austrian Grand Prix Circuit, how long did he spent at the pit stop at that same race?
SELECT raceId FROM races WHERE name = 'Austrian Grand Prix'	----- bird -----	formula_1
Please list the location coordinates of the circuits whose lap record is 1:29.488.

SELECT T1.`circuitId`, T1.`name`, T1.`location`, T1.`lat`, T1.`lng` FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN lapTimes AS T2 ON T1.`circuitId` = T2.`raceId` WHERE T2.`time` = '1:29.488'	----- bird -----	formula_1
What was the average time in milliseconds Lewis Hamilton spent at a pit stop during Formula_1 races?

What is the average lap time in milliseconds of all the lap records set on the various circuits in Italy?

Which player has the highest overall rating? Indicate the player's api id.

SELECT T1.`player_api_id` FROM Player_Attributes AS T1 INNER JOIN Player AS T2 ON T1.`player_api_id` = T2.`player_api_id` WHERE T1.`overall_rating` = ( SELECT MAX(T3.`overall_rating`) FROM Player_Attributes AS T3 )	----- bird -----	european_football_2
What is the height of the tallest player? Indicate his name.

SELECT Player.player_name FROM Player INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS T1 ON Player.player_api_id = T1.player_api_id WHERE T1.height = ( SELECT MAX(height) FROM Player_Attributes )	----- bird -----	european_football_2

Among the players with an overall rating between 60 to 65, how many players whose going to be in all of your attack moves instead of defensing?

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ( SELECT T1.`player_api_id` FROM Player_Attributes AS T1 WHERE T1.`overall_rating` BETWEEN 60 AND 65 ) AS T1 INNER JOIN ( SELECT T1.`player_api_id` FROM Player_Attributes AS T1 WHERE T1.`defensive_work_rate` = 'low' ) AS T2	----- bird -----	european_football_2
Who are the top 5 players who perform better in crossing actions? Indicate their player id.

SELECT T1.`player_api_id` FROM Player_Attributes AS T1 INNER JOIN Player AS T2 ON T1.`player_api_id` = T2.`player_api_id` WHERE T1.`crossing` IN ( SELECT T3.`crossing` FROM Player_Attributes AS T3 ORDER BY T3.`crossing` DESC LIMIT 5 )	----- bird -----	european_football_2
Which league had the most goals in the 2016 season?

SELECT League.name FROM League JOIN ( SELECT League.id, SUM(Match.home_team_goal + Match.away_team_goal) AS total_goals FROM League JOIN Match ON League.id = Match.league_id WHERE Match.season = '2015/2016' GROUP BY League.id ) AS subquery ORDER BY total_goals DESC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	european_football_2
Which home team had lost the fewest matches in the 2016 season?

SELECT T2.team_long_name FROM Team AS T2 JOIN ( SELECT T3.home_team_api_id, COUNT(*) AS total_losses FROM Match AS T3 WHERE T3.season = '2015/2016' AND (T3.home_team_goal - T3.away_team_goal) < 0 GROUP BY T3.home_team_api_id ) AS T4 ON T2.team_api_id = T4.home_team_api_id ORDER BY T4.total_losses ASC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	european_football_2
Indicate the full names of the top 10 players with the highest number of penalties.
SELECT T2.`player_name` FROM Player_Attributes AS T1 INNER JOIN Player AS T2 ON T1.`player_api_id` = T2.`player_api_id` ORDER BY T1.`penalties` DESC LIMIT 10	----- bird -----	european_football_2
In Scotland Premier League, which away team won the most during the 2010 season?

SELECT T2.away_team_api_id FROM League AS T1 JOIN Match AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.league_id WHERE T1.name = 'Scotland Premier League' AND T2.season = '2009/2010' GROUP BY T2.away_team_api_id ORDER BY SUM(T2.away_team_goal - T2.home_team_goal) DESC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	european_football_2
What are the speed in which attacks are put together of the top 4 teams with the highest build Up Play Speed?
SELECT T2.`team_long_name` FROM Team_Attributes AS T1 INNER JOIN Team AS T2 ON T1.`team_api_id` = T2.`team_api_id` ORDER BY T1.`buildUpPlaySpeed` DESC LIMIT 4	----- bird -----	european_football_2
Which League had the most matches end as draw in the 2016 season?

SELECT T1.name FROM League AS T1 INNER JOIN ( SELECT season, COUNT(*) AS draw_matches FROM Match WHERE season = '2015/2016' AND home_team_goal = away_team_goal GROUP BY season ORDER BY draw_matches DESC LIMIT 1 ) AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.season;	----- bird -----	european_football_2
At present, calculate for the player's age who have a sprint speed of no less than 97 between 2013 to 2015.

SELECT P.`gender` FROM Player P JOIN ( SELECT PA.player_api_id, (STRFTIME('%Y-%m-%d', 'now') - STRFTIME('%Y-%m-%d', PA.date)) AS AGE FROM Player_Attributes PA WHERE PA.sprint_speed >= 97 AND PA.date BETWEEN '2013-01-01 00:00:00' AND '2015-12-31 00:00:00' GROUP BY PA.player_api_id ) AS T ON P.`player_api_id` = T.`player_api_id` ORDER BY T.AGE ASC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	european_football_2

SELECT League.name, COUNT(Match.league_id) AS MatchCount FROM League JOIN Match ON League.id = Match.league_id GROUP BY League.id ORDER BY MatchCount DESC LIMIT 1	----- bird -----	european_football_2

List the players' api id who had the highest above average overall ratings in 2010.

SELECT P.`player_api_id` FROM Player_Attributes AS P INNER JOIN ( SELECT AVG(overall_rating) AS avg_rating FROM Player_Attributes WHERE substr(date,1,4) = '2010' ) AS T ON P.`overall_rating` > T.`avg_rating` WHERE substr(date,1,4) = '2010'	----- bird -----	european_football_2
Give the team_fifa_api_id of teams with more than 50 but less than 60 build-up play speed.

SELECT DISTINCT T2.`team_fifa_api_id` FROM Team_Attributes AS T1 INNER JOIN Team AS T2 ON T1.`team_api_id` = T2.`team_api_id` WHERE T1.`buildUpPlaySpeed` BETWEEN 51 AND 59	----- bird -----	european_football_2
List the long name of teams with above-average build-up play passing in 2012.

SELECT DISTINCT Team.team_long_name FROM Team INNER JOIN Team_Attributes ON Team.team_api_id = Team_Attributes.team_api_id INNER JOIN Player ON Team.team_api_id = Player.player_api_id INNER JOIN League ON Team.country_id = League.id INNER JOIN ( SELECT Team_Attributes.team_api_id, SUM(buildUpPlayPassing) / COUNT(Player.player_api_id) AS avg_buildUpPlayPassing FROM Team_Attributes INNER JOIN Player ON Team_Attributes.team_api_id = Player.player_api_id WHERE strftime('%Y', Player.date) = '2012' GROUP BY Team_Attributes.team_api_id ) AS AvgTeamPassing ON Team.team_api_id = AvgTeamPassing.team_api_id WHERE AvgTeamPassing.avg_buildUpPlayPassing > ( SELECT SUM(buildUpPlayPassing) / COUNT(DISTINCT Player.player_api_id) FROM Team_Attributes INNER JOIN Player ON Team_Attributes.team_api_id = Player.player_api_id WHERE strftime('%Y', Player.date) = '2012' ) AND strftime('%Y', Team.date) = '2012';	----- bird -----	european_football_2
Calculate the percentage of players who prefer left foot, who were born between 1987 and 1992.

SELECT ROUND( ( ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Player_Attributes pa JOIN Player p ON p.player_api_id = pa.player_api_id WHERE pa.preferred_foot = 'left' AND p.birthday BETWEEN '1987-01-01 00:00:00' AND '1992-12-31 00:00:00' ) / ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Player_Attributes pa JOIN Player p ON p.player_api_id = pa.player_api_id ) * 100, 2 ) AS percentage_left_footed_players_born_1987_to_1992 FROM Player_Attributes pa JOIN Player p ON p.player_api_id = pa.player_api_id WHERE p.birthday BETWEEN '1987-01-01 00:00:00' AND '1992-12-31 00:00:00' GROUP BY p.player_api_id;	----- bird -----	european_football_2
List the top 5 leagues in ascending order of the number of goals made in all seasons combined.

SELECT T2.id, SUM(T3.home_team_goal + T3.away_team_goal) AS total_goals FROM League AS T2 INNER JOIN ( SELECT T1.team_api_id, T3.league_id FROM Team AS T1 INNER JOIN Team_Attributes AS T3 ON T1.team_api_id = T3.team_api_id INNER JOIN Match AS T3 ON T1.team_api_id = T3.home_team_api_id OR T1.team_api_id = T3.away_team_api_id GROUP BY T1.team_api_id, T3.league_id ) AS T3 GROUP BY T2.id ORDER BY total_goals ASC LIMIT 5	----- bird -----	european_football_2

SELECT T1.team_long_name FROM Team_Attributes AS T1 INNER JOIN Team ON T1.team_api_id = Team.team_api_id INNER JOIN League ON Team.league_id = League.id INNER JOIN ( SELECT Match.home_team_api_id, SUM(Match.chanceCreationPassing) AS total_chance_creation_passing, COUNT(Match.id) AS match_count FROM Match WHERE Match.date >= '2014-01-01' AND Match.date < '2014-01-31' GROUP BY Match.home_team_api_id ) AS T2 ON Team.team_api_id = T2.home_team_api_id WHERE T1.buildUpPlayDribblingClass = 'Normal' GROUP BY T1.team_long_name HAVING total_chance_creation_passing / match_count < ( SELECT AVG(total_chance_creation_passing / match_count) FROM ( SELECT Match.home_team_api_id, SUM(Match.chanceCreationPassing) AS total_chance_creation_passing, COUNT(Match.id) AS match_count FROM Match WHERE Match.date >= '2014-01-01' AND Match.date < '2014-01-31' GROUP BY Match.home_team_api_id ) AS T3 ) ORDER BY total_chance_creation_passing / match_count DESC;	----- bird -----	european_football_2
List the name of leagues in which the average goals by the home team is higher than the away team in the 2009/2010 season.

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.`link_to_major` = T2.`major_id` WHERE T2.`department` = 'Education & Human Services' AND T2.`college` = 'College of Education & Human Services' AND T1.`position` = 'Member'	----- bird -----	student_club
What is the percentage of the events that went over budget?
SELECT (SUM(CASE WHEN T1.`remaining` < 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*)) * 100 FROM budget AS T1 INNER JOIN event AS T2 ON T1.`link_to_event` = T2.`event_id`	----- bird -----	student_club
Give the event ID, location, and status of events conducted from November 2019 to March 2020.
SELECT event_id, location, status FROM event WHERE event_date BETWEEN '2019-11-01' AND '2020-03-31' AND location IS NOT NULL;	----- bird -----	student_club
List the expenses that spend more than fifty dollars on average.
SELECT expense_id, expense_description, cost FROM expense WHERE cost > ( SELECT AVG(cost) FROM expense )	----- bird -----	student_club
Find the full name of members whose t-shirt size is extra large.
SELECT * FROM event;	----- bird -----	student_club
Calculate the percentage of zip codes that are PO boxes.
SELECT (COUNT(*) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM zip_code)) * 100 FROM zip_code WHERE type = 'PO Box'	----- bird -----	student_club
List the name and location of events that underspend its budget.

SELECT E.`event_name`, E.`location` FROM event AS E INNER JOIN ( SELECT B.`event_id`, SUM(B.`remaining`) AS total_remaining FROM budget AS B GROUP BY B.`event_id` ) AS BudgetRemaining ON E.`event_id` = BudgetRemaining.`event_id` WHERE BudgetRemaining.`total_remaining` > 0;	----- bird -----	student_club
Find the name and date of events with expenses for pizza that were more than fifty dollars but less than a hundred dollars.

SELECT DISTINCT E.`event_name`, E.`event_date` FROM event AS E INNER JOIN expense AS EX ON E.`event_id` = EX.`link_to_event` INNER JOIN budget AS B ON EX.`link_to_budget` = B.`budget_id` WHERE EX.`expense_description` = 'Pizza' AND EX.`cost` > 50 AND EX.`cost` < 100 GROUP BY E.`event_name`, E.`event_date`	----- bird -----	student_club
What is the name and major of members who had to spend more than a hundred dollars on an expense?

SELECT DISTINCT T1.`first_name`, T1.`last_name`, T4.`major_name` FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN expense AS T3 ON T1.`member_id` = T3.`link_to_member` INNER JOIN budget AS T2 ON T3.`link_to_budget` = T2.`budget_id` INNER JOIN major AS T4 ON T1.`link_to_major` = T4.`major_id` WHERE T2.`amount` > 100 AND T3.`cost` > 100	----- bird -----	student_club
In the events with more than forty incomes, list the city and country in which the event is happening.

SELECT DISTINCT T3.`city`, T3.`state` FROM zip_code AS T3 INNER JOIN member AS T5 ON T3.`zip` = T5.`zip` INNER JOIN attendance AS T6 ON T5.`member_id` = T6.`link_to_member` INNER JOIN ( SELECT E.`event_id` FROM event AS E INNER JOIN ( SELECT I.`link_to_event` FROM income AS I WHERE I.`amount` > 40 GROUP BY I.`link_to_event` HAVING COUNT(I.`income_id`) > 40 ) AS SubQuery1 ON E.`event_id` = SubQuery1.`link_to_event` ) AS T7 ON T6.`link_to_event` = T7.`event_id`	----- bird -----	student_club
Among the members who incurred expenses in more than one event, who paid the most amount?

SELECT m.member_id, MAX(e.cost) AS max_cost FROM expense e INNER JOIN ( SELECT a.link_to_member FROM attendance a INNER JOIN expense ex ON a.link_to_member = ex.link_to_member GROUP BY ex.link_to_member HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT a.link_to_event) > 1 ) AS subquery ON e.link_to_member = subquery.link_to_member INNER JOIN member m ON e.link_to_member = m.member_id GROUP BY m.member_id;	----- bird -----	student_club
What is the average amount paid by students in a position other than a member?
SELECT T1.`member_id`, T1.`position`, T1.`zip` FROM member AS T1 WHERE T1.`position` != 'Member'	----- bird -----	student_club
List the name of events with less than average parking cost.

SELECT DISTINCT E.`event_name` FROM `event` AS E JOIN ( SELECT B.`event_id`, AVG(B.`amount`) AS avg_cost FROM `budget` AS B WHERE B.`category` = 'Parking' AND B.`event_status` = 'Open' GROUP BY B.`event_id` ) AS B ON E.`event_id` = B.`event_id` WHERE E.`category` = 'Parking' AND E.`cost` < (SELECT MAX(avg_cost) FROM (SELECT AVG(B.`amount`) AS avg_cost FROM `budget` AS B WHERE B.`category` = 'Parking' AND B.`event_status` = 'Open' GROUP BY B.`event_id`) AS C) AND E.`event_status` = 'Open'	----- bird -----	student_club
What is the percentage of the cost for the game events?

SELECT (SUM(e.`cost`) / COUNT(DISTINCT ev.`event_id`)) * 100 AS percentage FROM expense AS e INNER JOIN attendance AS a ON e.`link_to_member` = a.`member_id` INNER JOIN event AS ev ON a.`link_to_event` = ev.`event_id` WHERE ev.`type` = 'Game' AND ev.`event_id` IS NOT NULL GROUP BY ev.`event_id`;	----- bird -----	student_club
Which budget allowed the most money for water, chips, and cookies?

SELECT MAX(T2.amount) FROM budget AS T2 INNER JOIN ( SELECT T1.link_to_budget FROM expense AS T1 WHERE T1.expense_description = 'Water, chips, cookies' GROUP BY T1.link_to_budget ) AS T3 ON T2.budget_id = T3.link_to_budget;	----- bird -----	student_club
List the full name of the top five members who spend the most money in the descending order of spending.

SELECT T1.`first_name`, T1.`last_name` FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN expense AS T2 ON T1.`member_id` = T2.`link_to_member` GROUP BY T1.`member_id` ORDER BY SUM(T2.`cost`) DESC LIMIT 5	----- bird -----	student_club
Give the full name and contact number of members who had to spend more than average on each expense.

-- Create indexes for faster querying CREATE INDEX idx_member_id ON member(member_id); CREATE INDEX idx_expense_link_to_member ON expense(link_to_member); CREATE INDEX idx_expense_link_to_budget ON expense(link_to_budget); CREATE INDEX idx_budget_link_to_event ON budget(link_to_event); CREATE INDEX idx_event_event_id ON event(event_id); CREATE INDEX idx_member_zip ON member(zip); CREATE INDEX idx_major_major_id ON major(major_id); CREATE INDEX idx_zip_zip_code ON zip_code(zip_code); -- Query to find the full name and contact number of members who had to spend more than average on each expense SELECT m.first_name || ' ' || m.last_name AS full_name, m.email AS contact_number FROM member m JOIN expense e ON m.member_id = e.link_to_member JOIN budget b ON e.link_to_budget = b.budget_id JOIN ( SELECT link_to_budget, AVG(cost) AS avg_cost FROM expense GROUP BY link_to_budget ) avg_costs ON b.budget_id = avg_costs.link_to_budget WHERE e.cost > avg_costs.avg_cost GROUP BY m.member_id;	----- bird -----	student_club
Calculate the difference in the percentage of members in Maine and Vermont.

SELECT (COUNT(*) * 100) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM member) AS percentage_vermont FROM member INNER JOIN zip_code ON member.`zip` = zip_code.`zip_code` WHERE zip_code.`state` = 'Vermont';	----- bird -----	student_club
What is the major of Garrett Gerke and which department does it belong to?
SELECT major.`department` FROM major WHERE major.`major_id` = ( SELECT major_id FROM member WHERE first_name = 'Garrett' AND last_name = 'Gerke' );	----- bird -----	student_club
Write the full name of the member who spent money for water, veggie tray and supplies and include the cost of it.

SELECT m.first_name, m.last_name, b.amount AS cost FROM member AS m JOIN attendance AS a ON m.member_id = a.link_to_member JOIN budget AS b ON a.link_to_event = b.link_to_event JOIN expense AS e ON m.member_id = e.link_to_member WHERE e.expense_description = 'Water, Veggie tray, supplies' AND b.category = 'Food' GROUP BY m.first_name, m.last_name, b.amount;	----- bird -----	student_club
List the last names of students under the Elementary Education major and include their phone numbers.
SELECT T1.`last_name`, T1.`phone` FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.`link_to_major` = T2.`major_id` WHERE T2.`major_name` = 'Elementary Education'	----- bird -----	student_club
What category was budgeted for the 'January Speaker' event and how much was the amount budgeted for that category?

SELECT budget.`category`, MAX(budget.`amount`) AS amount_budgeted FROM budget AS T1 INNER JOIN event AS T2 ON T1.`link_to_event` = T2.`event_id` WHERE T2.`event_name` = 'January Speaker' GROUP BY budget.`category`	----- bird -----	student_club
List the event names which were budgeted for the food.
SELECT T1.`event_name` FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN budget AS T2 ON T1.`event_id` = T2.`link_to_event` WHERE T2.`category` = 'Food'	----- bird -----	student_club
Write the full names of students who received funds on the date of 9/9/2019 and include the amount received.
SELECT T2.`amount` FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN income AS T2 ON T1.`member_id` = T2.`link_to_member` WHERE T2.`date_received` = '2019-09-09'	----- bird -----	student_club
Which budget category does the expense 'Posters' fall to?
SELECT category FROM budget WHERE budget_id = ( SELECT budget_id FROM expense WHERE expense_description = 'Posters' )	----- bird -----	student_club
Write the full name of the club member with the position of 'Secretary' and list which college the club member belongs to.

SELECT m.`first_name`, m.`last_name`, ma.`college` FROM member AS m JOIN attendance AS a ON m.`member_id` = a.`link_to_member` JOIN event AS e ON a.`link_to_event` = e.`event_id` JOIN zip_code AS za ON m.`zip` = za.`zip_code` JOIN major AS ma ON m.`link_to_major` = ma.`major_id` WHERE m.`position` = 'Secretary' AND e.`status` = 'Open' GROUP BY m.`first_name`, m.`last_name`, ma.`college`	----- bird -----	student_club
Calculate the total amount spent on speaker gifts and list the name of the event they were spent on.
SELECT e.`event_name` FROM event AS e INNER JOIN budget AS b ON e.`event_id` = b.`link_to_event` WHERE b.`category` = 'Speaker Gifts'	----- bird -----	student_club
Where is the hometown of Garrett Girke?
SELECT T1.city FROM zip_code AS T1 INNER JOIN member AS T3 ON T1.zip = T3.zip WHERE T3.first_name = 'Garrett' AND T3.last_name = 'Girke';	----- bird -----	student_club
Which student has the hometown of Lincolnton, North Carolina with the zip code of 28092? List their full name and position.

SELECT member.first_name, member.last_name, major.major_name FROM member JOIN major ON member.link_to_major = major.major_id WHERE member.member_id = ( SELECT member.member_id FROM member JOIN zip_code ON member.zip = zip_code.zip_code WHERE zip_code.zip_code = ( SELECT zip_code.zip_code FROM zip_code WHERE city = 'Lincolnton' AND state = 'North Carolina' ) AND member.zip = 28092 )	----- bird -----	student_club
How many gas stations in CZE has Premium gas?

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.`GasStationID`) FROM gasstations AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.`ChainID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T1.`Country` = 'CZE' AND T1.`Segment` = 'Premium'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the ratio of costumers who pay in EUR against customers who pay in CZK?
SELECT ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Currency = 'EUR' ) / ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Currency = 'CZK' ) AS ratio	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
In 2012, who had the least consumption in LAM?

SELECT ym.CustomerID, MIN(ym.Consumption) AS MinConsumption FROM yearmonth ym JOIN customers c ON ym.CustomerID = c.CustomerID WHERE c.Segment = 'LAM' AND strftime('%Y', ym.Date) = '2012' GROUP BY ym.CustomerID ORDER BY MinConsumption ASC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What was the average monthly consumption of customers in SME for the year 2013?

SELECT AVG(Consumption) / 12 AS AverageMonthlyConsumption FROM ( SELECT strftime('%Y', T1.`Date`) AS Year, MONTH(T1.`Date`) AS Month, SUM(T1.`Consumption`) AS Consumption FROM yearmonth AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T2.`Segment` = 'SME' AND T1.`Date` BETWEEN '2013-01-01' AND '2013-12-31' GROUP BY Year, Month ) AS T4	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which customers, paying in CZK, consumed the most gas in 2011?

SELECT T1.`CustomerID`, SUM(T1.`Consumption`) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T1.`Date` BETWEEN '20110101' AND '20111231' AND T2.`Currency` = 'CZK' GROUP BY T1.`CustomerID` ORDER BY SUM(T1.`Consumption`) DESC LIMIT 1	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How many customers in KAM had a consumption of less than 30,000 for the year 2012?

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T2.`Segment` = 'KAM' AND T1.`Date` BETWEEN '201201' AND '201212' AND T1.`Consumption` < 30000	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What was the difference in gas consumption between CZK-paying customers and EUR-paying customers in 2012?

SELECT (SELECT SUM(y2.`Consumption`) FROM yearmonth AS y2 INNER JOIN customers AS c2 ON y2.`CustomerID` = c2.`CustomerID` WHERE c2.`Currency` = 'CZK' AND y2.`Date` BETWEEN '20120101' AND '20121231') - (SELECT SUM(y2.`Consumption`) FROM yearmonth AS y2 INNER JOIN customers AS c2 ON y2.`CustomerID` = c2.`CustomerID` WHERE c2.`Currency` = 'EUR' AND y2.`Date` BETWEEN '20120101' AND '20121231') AS Consumption_difference	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which year recorded the most gas use paid in EUR?

SELECT strftime('%Y', yearmonth.`Date`) AS Year, SUM(yearmonth.`Consumption`) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.`CustomerID` = customers.`CustomerID` WHERE customers.`Currency` = 'EUR' GROUP BY Year ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which segment had the least consumption?

SELECT c.`Segment`, MIN(y.`Consumption`) AS `LeastConsumption` FROM customers AS c JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.`CustomerID` = y.`CustomerID` GROUP BY c.`Segment` ORDER BY `LeastConsumption` ASC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which year recorded the most consumption of gas paid in CZK?

SELECT strftime('%Y', Y1.`Date`) AS Year, SUM(Y1.`Consumption`) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth AS Y1 INNER JOIN customers AS C1 ON Y1.`CustomerID` = C1.`CustomerID` WHERE C1.`Currency` = 'CZK' GROUP BY strftime('%Y', Y1.`Date`) ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What was the gas consumption peak month for SME customers in 2013?

SELECT YM.`Date` AS PeakMonth FROM ( SELECT YM.`Date`, MAX(YM.`Consumption`) AS PeakConsumption FROM yearmonth AS YM INNER JOIN customers AS C ON YM.`CustomerID` = C.`CustomerID` WHERE C.`Segment` = 'SME' AND YM.`Date` LIKE '2013%' GROUP BY YM.`Date` ) AS PeakMonthData ORDER BY PeakConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the difference in the annual average consumption of the customers with the least amount of consumption paid in CZK for 2013 between SME and LAM, LAM and KAM, and KAM and SME?

SELECT T2.Segment, AVG(T1.Consumption) AS AnnualAverageConsumption FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY T2.Segment HAVING T1.Consumption IS NOT NULL ORDER BY AnnualAverageConsumption ASC;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which of the three segmentsSME, LAM and KAMhas the biggest and lowest percentage increases in consumption paid in EUR between 2012 and 2013?

SELECT T1.`Segment`, ((T1.`Consumption_2013` - T1.`Consumption_2012`) / T1.`Consumption_2013`) * 100 AS `Percentage_Increase` FROM ( SELECT YM.`CustomerID`, C.`Segment`, SUM(CASE WHEN YM.`Date` LIKE '201201' THEN YM.`Consumption` ELSE 0 END) AS `Consumption_2012`, SUM(CASE WHEN YM.`Date` LIKE '201312' THEN YM.`Consumption` ELSE 0 END) AS `Consumption_2013` FROM yearmonth AS YM INNER JOIN customers AS C ON YM.`CustomerID` = C.`CustomerID` WHERE C.`Segment` IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY YM.`CustomerID`, C.`Segment` ) AS T1 ORDER BY `Percentage_Increase` DESC;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How much did customer 6 consume in total between August and November 2013?
SELECT SUM(T1.`Consumption`) FROM yearmonth AS T1 WHERE T1.`CustomerID` = 6 AND T1.`Date` BETWEEN '201308' AND '201311'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How many more "discount" gas stations does the Czech Republic have compared to Slovakia?
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM gasstations WHERE ChainID IN ( SELECT ChainID FROM gasstations WHERE Segment = 'Discount' ) AND Country = 'SVK'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How much more was customer 7 consuming in April 2013 than customer 5?

SELECT ( SELECT `Consumption` FROM yearmonth WHERE `CustomerID` = 7 AND `Date` = '201304' ) - ( SELECT `Consumption` FROM yearmonth WHERE `CustomerID` = 5 AND `Date` = '201304' ) AS Difference	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Is it true that more SMEs pay in Czech koruna than in euros? If so, how many more?

SELECT ( SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.CustomerID) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Currency = 'CZK' ) - ( SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.CustomerID) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Currency = 'EUR' ) AS Difference	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which LAM customer used the Euro as their currency and had the highest consumption in October 2013?

SELECT T1.CustomerID, MAX(T2.Consumption) AS MaxConsumption FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T1.Currency = 'EUR' AND T2.Date LIKE '201310%' GROUP BY T1.CustomerID HAVING MaxConsumption = ( SELECT MAX(Consumption) FROM yearmonth WHERE Date LIKE '201310%' )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Who among KAM's customers consumed the most? How much did it consume?
SELECT MAX(`Consumption`) FROM yearmonth WHERE `CustomerID` IN ( SELECT `CustomerID` FROM customers WHERE `Segment` = 'KAM' )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How much did the KAM customers consume in total in May 2013?
SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) FROM yearmonth y JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID WHERE c.Segment = 'KAM' AND y.Date LIKE '201305%'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How many percent of LAM customer consumed more than 46.73?

SELECT ( ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.`CustomerID` = customers.`CustomerID` WHERE customers.`Segment` = 'LAM' AND yearmonth.`Consumption` > 46.73 ) / ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Segment = 'LAM' ) * 100 ) AS percentage	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which country has more "value for money" gas stations? Please give a total number of "value for money" gas stations in each country.

SELECT g.`Country`, COUNT(*) AS "Value for Money Gas Stations" FROM gasstations AS g INNER JOIN gasstations AS g2 ON g.`ChainID` = g2.`ChainID` WHERE g2.`Segment` = 'Value for money' GROUP BY g.`Country` ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What percentage of KAM customers pay in euros?

SELECT ROUND( ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT T1.`CustomerID` FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T1.`Segment` = 'KAM' AND T2.`Currency` = 'EUR' AND T2.`Currency` IS NOT NULL ) AS SubQuery ) / ( SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Segment = 'KAM' AND Currency IS NOT NULL ) * 100, 2 ) AS percentage	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
In February 2012, what percentage of customers consumed more than 528.3?

SELECT (num_customers / total_consumption) * 100 AS percentage FROM ( SELECT SUM(`Consumption`) AS total_consumption FROM yearmonth WHERE `Date` LIKE '201202%' ) AS subquery1, ( SELECT COUNT(*) AS num_customers FROM yearmonth WHERE `Consumption` > 528.3 AND `Date` LIKE '201202%' ) AS subquery2	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What percentage of Slovakian gas stations are premium?

SELECT (PremiumGasStations / TotalGasStations) * 100 AS PercentageOfPremiumGasStations FROM ( SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT GasStationID) AS TotalGasStations FROM gasstations WHERE Country = 'SVK' ) AS TotalGasStationsTable, ( SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT GasStationID) AS PremiumGasStations FROM gasstations WHERE Country = 'SVK' AND Segment = 'Premium' ) AS PremiumGasStationsTable	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which client ID consumed the most in September 2013?
SELECT T1.`CustomerID` FROM yearmonth AS T1 WHERE T1.`Date` = '201309' ORDER BY T1.`Consumption` DESC LIMIT 1	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which client segment consumed the least in September 2013?

SELECT T2.`Segment` FROM ( SELECT `CustomerID`, SUM(`Consumption`) AS `TotalConsumption` FROM `yearmonth` WHERE `Date` = '201309' GROUP BY `CustomerID` ) AS T1 INNER JOIN `customers` AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` ORDER BY T1.`TotalConsumption` ASC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which SME customer consumed the least in June 2012?

SELECT T1.`Consumption` FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T2.`Segment` = 'SME' AND T1.`Date` = '201206' ORDER BY T1.`Consumption` ASC LIMIT 1	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the highest monthly consumption in the year 2012?
SELECT MAX(`Consumption`) FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTR(`Date`, 1, 4) = '2012'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the biggest monthly consumption of the customers who use euro as their currency?

SELECT MAX(monthly_consumption) AS MaxMonthlyConsumption FROM ( SELECT `CustomerID`, SUM(Consumption) / 12 AS monthly_consumption FROM yearmonth GROUP BY `CustomerID` ) AS subquery WHERE `CustomerID` IN ( SELECT `CustomerID` FROM customers WHERE `Currency` = 'EUR' )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Please list the product description of the products consumed in September, 2013.

SELECT DISTINCT P.`Description` FROM products AS P INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T1 ON P.`ProductID` = T1.`ProductID` INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T2.`Date` LIKE '201309%'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Please list the countries of the gas stations with transactions taken place in June, 2013.

SELECT DISTINCT gs.Country FROM gasstations gs JOIN transactions_1k t ON gs.GasStationID = t.GasStationID JOIN yearmonth ym ON t.CustomerID = ym.CustomerID WHERE ym.Date LIKE '201306%' ORDER BY gs.Country ASC;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Please list the chains of the gas stations with transactions in euro.
SELECT DISTINCT T1.`ChainID` FROM gasstations AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.`GasStationID` = T2.`GasStationID` WHERE T2.`Price` IS NOT NULL	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Please list the product description of the products bought in transactions in euro.

SELECT DISTINCT P.`Description` FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN products AS P ON T1.`ProductID` = P.`ProductID` INNER JOIN customers AS C ON T1.`CustomerID` = C.`CustomerID` WHERE C.`Currency` = 'EUR' ORDER BY P.`Description` ASC;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the average total price of the transactions taken place in January, 2012?

SELECT AVG(TotalPrice) AS AveragePrice FROM ( SELECT SUM(T1.Price) AS TotalPrice FROM transactions_1k AS T1 JOIN yearmonth AS YM ON T1.CustomerID = YM.CustomerID WHERE YM.Date LIKE '2012-01%' GROUP BY YM.CustomerID ) AS SubQuery;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Among the customers who paid in euro, how many of them have a monthly consumption of over 1000?

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT ym.`CustomerID` FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.`CustomerID` = c.`CustomerID` WHERE c.`Currency` = 'EUR' AND ym.`Consumption` > 1000 ) AS ym_filtered	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Please list the product descriptions of the transactions taken place in the gas stations in the Czech Republic.

SELECT DISTINCT T1.`Description` FROM products AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.`ProductID` = T2.`ProductID` INNER JOIN gasstations AS T3 ON T2.`GasStationID` = T3.`GasStationID` WHERE T3.`Country` = 'CZE'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Please list the disparate time of the transactions taken place in the gas stations from chain no. 11.
SELECT DISTINCT T1.`Time` FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.`GasStationID` = T2.`GasStationID` WHERE T2.`ChainID` = 11	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How many transactions taken place in the gas station in the Czech Republic are with a price of over 1000?

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.`GasStationID` = T2.`GasStationID` WHERE T2.`Country` = 'CZE' AND T1.`Price` > 1000	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Among the transactions made in the gas stations in the Czech Republic, how many of them are taken place after 2012/1/1?

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ( SELECT T1.`TransactionID`, T1.`Date`, T1.`Time`, T1.`CustomerID`, T1.`CardID`, T1.`GasStationID`, T1.`ProductID`, T1.`Amount`, T1.`Price` FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.`GasStationID` = T2.`GasStationID` WHERE T2.`Country` = 'CZE' AND T1.`Date` > '2012-01-01' ) AS T3	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the average total price of the transactions taken place in gas stations in the Czech Republic?
SELECT AVG(T1.`Price`) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.`GasStationID` = T2.`GasStationID` WHERE T2.`Country` = 'CZE'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
For the customers who paid in the euro, what is their average total price of the transactions?
SELECT AVG(T1.`Price`) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T2.`Currency` = 'EUR'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which customer paid the most in 2012/8/25?

SELECT T3.`Segment` FROM customers AS T3 WHERE T3.`CustomerID` = ( SELECT T2.`CustomerID` FROM ( SELECT T1.`CustomerID`, SUM(T1.`Amount`) AS TotalAmount FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.`Date` = '2012-08-25' GROUP BY T1.`CustomerID` ) AS T2 ORDER BY T2.`TotalAmount` DESC LIMIT 1 )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which country's gas station had the first paid cusomer in 2012/8/25?

SELECT DISTINCT T2.`Country` FROM gasstations AS T2 INNER JOIN ( SELECT T1.`GasStationID` FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.`Date` = '2012-08-25' AND T1.`Amount` > 0 ORDER BY T1.`Date` ASC LIMIT 1 ) AS T3 ON T2.`GasStationID` = T3.`GasStationID`	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What kind of currency did the customer paid at 16:25:00 in 2012/8/24?

SELECT T1.`Currency` FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T2.`TransactionID` = ( SELECT TransactionID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Time = '16:25:00' AND Date = '2012-08-24' )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What segment did the customer have at 2012/8/23 21:20:00?

SELECT T2.`Segment` FROM customers AS T2 INNER JOIN ( SELECT T1.* FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.`Date` = '2012-08-23' AND T1.`Time` = '21:20:00' ) AS T3 ON T2.`CustomerID` = T3.`CustomerID`	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
How many transactions were paid in EUR in the morning of 2012/8/26?
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM transactions_1k WHERE `Date` = '2012-08-26' AND `Time` < '13:00:00'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
For the earliest customer, what segment did he/she have?
SELECT Segment FROM customers WHERE CustomerID = ( SELECT CustomerID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Date = ( SELECT MIN(Date) FROM transactions_1k ) )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
For the deal happened at 2012/8/24 12:42:00, which country was it?

SELECT Country FROM gasstations WHERE GasStationID = ( SELECT GasStationID FROM transactions_1k WHERE TransactionID = ( SELECT TransactionID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Date = '2012-08-24' AND Time = '12:42:00' ) )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What was the product id of the transaction happened at 2012/8/23 21:20:00?
SELECT ProductID FROM transactions_1k WHERE TransactionID = ( SELECT TransactionID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Date = '2012-08-23' AND Time = '21:20:00' )	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
For the customer who paid 124.05 in 2012/8/24, how much did he/she spend during the January of 2012? And what is the date and expenses exactly?

SELECT ym.`Date`, MAX(t.`Amount`) AS Expenses FROM transactions_1k t JOIN yearmonth ym ON t.`CustomerID` = ym.`CustomerID` WHERE t.`CustomerID` = ( SELECT `CustomerID` FROM transactions_1k WHERE `Amount` = 124.05 AND `Date` = '2012-08-24' LIMIT 1 ) AND ym.`Date` BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2012-01-31' GROUP BY ym.`Date` ORDER BY ym.`Date` ASC;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
For all the transactions happened during 8:00-9:00 in 2012/8/26, how many happened in CZE?

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.TransactionID) AS NumberOfTransactions FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS GS ON T1.GasStationID = GS.GasStationID WHERE T1.Time BETWEEN '08:00:00' AND '09:00:00' AND T1.Date = '2012-08-26' AND GS.Country = 'CZE';	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
There's one customer spent 214582.17 in the June of 2013, which currency did he/she use?

SELECT c.`Currency` FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN ( SELECT t.`CustomerID` FROM transactions_1k AS t INNER JOIN yearmonth AS ym ON t.`CustomerID` = ym.`CustomerID` WHERE ym.`Date` LIKE '201306%' GROUP BY t.`CustomerID` HAVING MAX(t.`Amount`) = 214582.17 ) AS subquery ON c.`CustomerID` = subquery.`CustomerID`	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which country was the card owner of No.667467 in?
SELECT DISTINCT T3.`Country` FROM transactions_1k AS T2 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T3 ON T2.`GasStationID` = T3.`GasStationID` WHERE T2.`CardID` = 667467	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What's the nationality of the customer who spent 548.4 in 2012/8/24?

SELECT DISTINCT c.`Segment` FROM customers AS c JOIN transactions_1k AS t ON c.`CustomerID` = t.`CustomerID` JOIN yearmonth AS ym ON c.`CustomerID` = ym.`CustomerID` WHERE t.`Amount` = 548.4 AND t.`Date` = '2012-08-24' AND ym.`Consumption` IS NOT NULL GROUP BY c.`Segment`	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the percentage of the customers who used EUR in 2012/8/25?

SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT T2.CustomerID) / (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT CustomerID) FROM yearmonth WHERE Date = '2012-08-25')) * 100 AS percentage FROM yearmonth AS T2 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T1 ON T2.CustomerID = T1.CustomerID INNER JOIN customers AS C ON T1.CustomerID = C.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-25' AND C.Currency = 'EUR' GROUP BY T2.CustomerID;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
For the customer who paid 634.8 in 2012/8/25, what was the consumption decrease rate from Year 2012 to 2013?

SELECT (y2012.Consumption - y2013.Consumption) / y2012.Consumption AS consumption_decrease_rate FROM (SELECT ym.CustomerID, SUM(ym.Consumption) AS Consumption FROM yearmonth ym JOIN customers c ON ym.CustomerID = c.CustomerID WHERE ym.Date = '2012-08-24' AND c.CustomerID IN (SELECT DISTINCT CustomerID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Amount = 634.8 AND Date = '2012-08-25') GROUP BY ym.CustomerID) AS y2012 JOIN (SELECT ym.CustomerID, SUM(ym.Consumption) AS Consumption FROM yearmonth ym JOIN customers c ON ym.CustomerID = c.CustomerID WHERE ym.Date = '2013-08-24' AND c.CustomerID IN (SELECT DISTINCT CustomerID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Amount = 634.8 AND Date = '2012-08-25') GROUP BY ym.CustomerID) AS y2013 ON y2012.CustomerID = y2013.CustomerID;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which gas station has the highest amount of revenue?

SELECT T1.GasStationID, MAX(T1.TotalRevenue) AS HighestRevenue FROM ( SELECT T1.GasStationID, SUM(T1.Amount * T1.Price) AS TotalRevenue FROM transactions_1k AS T1 GROUP BY T1.GasStationID ) AS T1 GROUP BY T1.GasStationID ORDER BY HighestRevenue DESC LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the percentage of "premium" against the overall segment in "SVK"?

SELECT ( SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T2.GasStationID) FROM transactions_1k AS T2 JOIN gasstations ON T2.GasStationID = gasstations.GasStationID WHERE gasstations.Country = 'SVK' AND gasstations.Segment = 'Premium' ) / ( SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T2.GasStationID) FROM transactions_1k AS T2 JOIN gasstations ON T2.GasStationID = gasstations.GasStationID WHERE gasstations.Country = 'SVK' ) * 100 AS percentage	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
What is the amount spent by customer "38508" at the gas stations? How much had the customer spent in January 2012?

SELECT SUM(T1.`Amount`) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T1.`CustomerID` = 38508 AND T2.`Date` LIKE '201201%'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which are the top five best selling products? Please state the full name of them.

SELECT T1.`Description` FROM ( SELECT T1.`ProductID`, SUM(T2.`Amount`) AS `TotalSales` FROM products AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.`ProductID` = T2.`ProductID` GROUP BY T1.`ProductID` ORDER BY `TotalSales` DESC LIMIT 5 ) AS T3 INNER JOIN products AS T1 ON T3.`ProductID` = T1.`ProductID`	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Who is the top spending customer and how much is the average price per single item purchased by this customer? What currency was being used?

SELECT c.`Currency`, AVG(t.`Price` / t.`Amount`) AS AvgPricePerItem FROM customers AS c JOIN ( SELECT t.`CustomerID` FROM transactions_1k AS t WHERE t.`Price` IS NOT NULL AND t.`Amount` IS NOT NULL GROUP BY t.`CustomerID` ORDER BY SUM(t.`Amount`) DESC LIMIT 1 ) AS top_customer ON c.`CustomerID` = top_customer.`CustomerID` JOIN transactions_1k AS t ON c.`CustomerID` = t.`CustomerID` GROUP BY c.`Currency`	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
Which country had the gas station that sold the most expensive product id No.2 for one unit?

SELECT T2.`Country` FROM gasstations AS T2 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T3 ON T2.`GasStationID` = T3.`GasStationID` WHERE T3.`ProductID` = ( SELECT T1.`ProductID` FROM products AS T1 WHERE T1.`ProductID` = 2 LIMIT 1 ) ORDER BY T3.`Price` DESC LIMIT 1	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
For all the people who paid more than 29.00 per unit of product id No.5. Give their consumption status in the August of 2012.

SELECT T1.`Consumption` FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN ( SELECT DISTINCT T1.`CustomerID` FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.`ProductID` = T2.`ProductID` WHERE T2.`ProductID` = 5 AND T1.`Price` / T1.`Amount` > 29.00 ) AS T2 ON T1.`CustomerID` = T2.`CustomerID` WHERE T1.`Date` LIKE '201208%'	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
